#drag and select an area to capture
r=[]
e=[]


import pyautogui # tek monitor kullanıyor ve tuş dinleme yok
from pynput.mouse import Listener, Button
from PIL import Image


def on_click(x, y, button, pressed):
    print('{0} at {1}'.format('Pressed' if pressed else 'Released',(x, y)))
    global r
    r.append(x)
    global e
    e.append(y)
    if not pressed:
        # Stop listener
        return False


# Initialize the Listener to monitor mouse clicks
with Listener(on_click=on_click) as listener:
    listener.join()


print(r[0],e[0],r[1],e[1])
r.sort()
e.sort()
area=r[0],e[0],r[1]-r[0],e[1]-e[0]
print(area)





img = pyautogui.screenshot(region=(area)) # çek ve değişkene ata
img.save('im.png') # Save the image
